(97, 1, '2018-02-13 19:46:33', '2018-02-13 19:46:33', '[nextpage title="1"]\r\n\r\nThomas hood of [xxx]\r\nA vyag pretendyd by the grase of god to the endyes anno 1586 1586 and saffa[xxx]\r\n\r\nNycolas moore was shypp[xx]\r\nThe 16 day of July\r\nNycolas gaffyrd ….xx[x]\r\nAndrew solyde[?]..\r\nJohn myttyn\r\nTHomas dunmore\r\nRychard Bacheler\r\nSheppard\r\nEdward Audy\r\nJohn Loves\r\nGyls Gosse[?]\r\nWillyam wycks\r\nJohn Mychall\r\nThomas\r\nRobert pulman was shyppyd the 5 daye of August\r\n\r\n[/nextpage]\r\n[nextpage title="2"]\r\n\r\n1586 June Precept\r\n \r\nThe 24 days of June our men entryd wagys at graves end\r\n \r\nA voyage pretendyd to the Indyes set forth by the good earle of cumberland wyth 2 shyps and a pynnys mte wytheryngton beJng captyn of the athmerall and mte lyster of the vys athmerall\r\n \r\nThe 26 daye of June we departyd from gravesend into tylbrehop and there we ankeryd tyll the nex[t d]ay\r\n \r\nThe 27 departyd from tylbrehop and cam to the north forland and thar we ankored\r\n \r\nThe 28 daye we cam in to the downs the wynd being westerlye and thare we Ankeryd\r\n\r\n[/nextpage]\r\n[nextpage title="3"]\r\n\r\nJune 1586\r\nThe 29 Daye of we wayed in the douns wyth the wynd west norwest and when we cam about The south forland we met the wynd at the southwest and put us back agayn in to the douns\r\n\r\nThe 30 daye of June we wayd in the douns wyth the wynd at west norwest and of a douer we met The wynd At southwest and that tyd we turnet up in to rumny bay And thare we ankered in 15 fatha[m]\r\n\r\nThe 30 day of June being the last daye of the moonth at 9 Aclok at nyt we wayd in rumny bay wyth the wynd at west and the furst day of July in the mornyng at 4 aclok we cam to an anker under do dungynes in 16 fatham of the norest part of the nos\r\n\r\n[/nextpage]\r\n[nextpage title="4"]\r\n\r\nJuly 1586\r\n \r\nThe fyrst day of Julye at 10 of the clok in the fornoone we wayd At the nos wyth the wynd at southwest and wythin one our Jt proved fog and very thycke  Thar we war parforsyd to Anker in 16 fatham water for  Jt was to Thycke thar we durst not sycke in wyth the shor and thar we ryd in the se all that daye and All that nyt beyng very thyck and durst not dell wyth the shore\r\n\r\nThe second day of July we wayd beyng in 16 fathem short of ry And went to wyndward the wynd being At sou souwe[st] wyth thyck and fog and about 3 of the clok At Afternoone J[t] clyred up and the wynd cam esterlye we being of fayerlyt\r\nLee \r\nAnd we were hens west southwest \r\n\r\n[/nextpage]\r\n[nextpage title="5"]\r\n\r\nJuly 1586\r\nThe 3 day of Julye About 5 of te clok in the morning the Eyll of wyt bor west from us the wynd being at est northest And we going west south west and the same After noone about 7 of the clock at nyt we ware close of portland\r\n\r\nThe 4 day of July being mondaye before 6 of the clock in the mornyng we cam in to dartmouth rang the wynd being At est northest and we went in to the haven\r\n\r\nThe 23 daye of July being saturdaye we departyd from dartmouth the wynd being All northerly And about 12 of the clok J provyd callmwe being short of the start and that tyd we we Ankered About 6 of the clok  in the evynyng the wynd being west And by south \r\n\r\n[/nextpage]', 'Hood''s Log', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '63-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-02-13 19:46:33', '2018-02-13 19:46:33', '', 63, 'http://www.scg52.com/Archive/?p=97', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
